This paper deals with the issue of network failures and proposes a new concept of tunable survivability for improving network performance. The paper focuses on the optimization of additive criteria such as delay and cost, which are important in the context of network design. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.RO (Robotics and Control).
